.TH "TD\-INFO" "1" "2026" "TARDIS Manual"
.SH NAME
td\-info \- display calendar metadata for a date
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]td info\f[R] [\f[I]DATE\f[R]] [\f[I]OPTIONS\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f[B]td info\f[R] shows detailed calendar metadata for the given date
expression.
When no expression is provided, it defaults to \[lq]now\[rq].
.PP
The output includes fields such as: year, month, day, weekday, week
number, quarter, day of year, Julian Day Number, Unix epoch, timezone,
and whether the date falls in a leap year or during daylight saving
time.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]\-j\f[R], \f[B]\-\-json\f[R]
Output as a JSON object with all metadata fields.
.TP
\f[B]\-n\f[R], \f[B]\-\-no\-newline\f[R]
Suppress the trailing newline.
.TP
\f[B]\-\-now\f[R] \f[I]DATETIME\f[R]
Override the current time (RFC 3339).
.TP
\f[B]\-t\f[R], \f[B]\-\-timezone\f[R] \f[I]TZ\f[R]
Timezone for resolution (IANA/Olson ID).
.TP
\f[B]\-v\f[R], \f[B]\-\-verbose\f[R]
Print verbose diagnostics to stderr.
.TP
\f[B]\-h\f[R], \f[B]\-\-help\f[R]
Print help information.
.SH EXAMPLES
Info for the current date:
.IP
.EX
td info \-t UTC
.EE
.PP
Info for a specific date:
.IP
.EX
td info \[dq]2025\-12\-25\[dq] \-t UTC
.EE
.PP
Info for a natural\-language expression:
.IP
.EX
td info \[dq]next friday\[dq] \-t UTC
.EE
.PP
JSON output with all metadata fields:
.IP
.EX
td info \[dq]2025\-01\-01\[dq] \-\-json \-t UTC
.EE
.PP
Info with a specific timezone:
.IP
.EX
td info \[dq]now\[dq] \-t America/Sao_Paulo
.EE
.PP
Info for a relative expression:
.IP
.EX
td info \[dq]3 days ago\[dq] \-t UTC
.EE
